    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No.893.811/128.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs has asked me to make known to you his
                    Government’s appreciation of the good offices of our Government in the matter of
                    the Huai River conservancy and particularly of its action in making available
                    for this purpose so distinguished an engineer as Colonel Sibert; and he further
                    requested me to express through the Department to the American Red Cross the
                    gratitude of the Chinese Government for the assistance of that society in making
                    the necessary arrangements with American financial and industrial interests and
                    for its generosity in assuming so liberal a financial responsibility in
                    connection with the preliminary survey which is about to be undertaken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
